somalibench_eval — dual license
================================

Code (everything under src/, configs/, and analysis scripts) is released under
the MIT License.

Aggregate analysis outputs (data/results/, data/figures/, paper/) are released
under CC-BY-NC-4.0, inheriting the license of the underlying SomaliBench v0
benchmark this study evaluates.

Raw model responses captured during evaluation (data/responses/,
data/classifications/, data/spot_checks/) are NOT released. They are kept on
disk for reproducibility audit but are not redistributed.

Responsible-use notice
----------------------

This repository contains code that orchestrates inference on a published
harmful-intent safety benchmark for the purpose of measuring model refusal
behavior. By using this code you agree:

1. You will use it only to measure / audit model safety behavior, not to
   produce a system that complies with harmful requests.
2. You will not redistribute the raw harmful-compliance generations captured
   during evaluation.
3. You will cite both this study and SomaliBench v0 in any derived work.

